PLAYMATE settled at the rear near but off the rail, moved out a bit further on the far turn, was tipped out further in upper stretch for room, once engaged rallied strongly but too late. PAINTED GLORY was forwardly-positioned four to five deep in the early going appearing to fight the rider's restraint, was still under a hold early up the backstretch and lost ground and position as rivals advanced outside heading to the far turn, swung out eight wide for the drive and came again to finish up strongly. ANITA MARGARITA moved to the fore to set the early pace racing off the rail in the two path, was overtaken at the three-quarter and settled off that rival and inside content to attend, inherited the lead again when that one weakened, was clear into upper stretch, challenged in mid-stretch, yielded late. ANDROMACHE was checked heading into the first turn when in tight and on heels, raced three to four wide toward the back on that bend, advanced between runners three wide into and on the far turn, angled nearer the rail for room at the top of the stretch, kicked on mildly. MONEY BEETS settled off the pace two to three wide, moved out and advanced outside foes five to six wide up the backstretch, was within range on the far turn, lacked the needed late kick. PRINCESSONAMISSION raced up close in pursuit of the leaders three to four wide, asked for more at the five-sixteenths but had nothing. LADY XI settled at the rear outside racing three to four wide, swung eight deep into upper stretch, failed to threaten. QUICKER TREAT was caught six wide through the first turn, moved up to garner more forward position heading up the backstretch, was in range four to five deep on the far turn but faltered and faded. SUPER SICILY was in tight quarters heading to the first turn, moved forward under encouragement outside foes five wide on the first turn to take the lead at the three-quarters, set the pace from outside the earlier leader racing three deep up the backstretch, retreated from the seven-sixteenths.
